name: NoodlyInvesting
description: A Capstone Project to create a informational and user friendly application to educate users about investing in stocks. Mobile GUI front-end made with Android Studio and coded in Java. Microservice SpringBoot back-end using Netflix/Eureka and Zuul to create a RESTful API.

name: Ikigai
description: A project made during a Cloud Development Course to test my skills with AWS. The application was made to allow users to add and remove tasks for a to-do list. Upon completion of the tasks it will "grow" the users personal beehive. The back-end application runs on AWS Elastic Beanstalk using a Java SpringBoot microservice RESTful API. The front-end runs locally using NodeJS and Express, it will make API calls to the back-end to gather necessary data. The email-lambda runs on AWS Lambda only being triggered by events put into a AWS Simple Queue Service bucket.
